&nbsp;Former Kibwezi Member of Parliament (MP), Kalembe Ndile, was injured in a road accident along the Nairobi-Mombasa Highway on Saturday morning. According to Athi River traffic base, the accident happened at Devki area involving a Subaru Forester driven by Mr Ndile and a Mercedes Benz by one Nicodemus. ALSO READ: NTSA still has work to do to make roads safe Ndile, who was headed to Mombasa collided head on with the Mercedes Benz which was heading in the oppposite direction. The former legislator sustained a fracture on the right leg and left hand. He was rushed to Shalom Community Hospital where he was admitted. More to follow...